claim.claim-text:
1. A method to align a wafer in a double patterning lithography process, comprising:
depositing, a first resist layer having a first optical characteristic;
forming at least one alignment mark having the first optical characteristic in the first resist layer;
developing the first resist layer; and
depositing a second resist layer, having a second optical characteristic, over the first resist layer, wherein combination of the first and second resist layers and the alignment mark being configured and arranged such that radiation of a pre-determined wavelength incident on the alignment mark produces a first or higher order diffraction as a function of the first and second optical characteristics.
